e way, based on the fact that competing libraries do already have this functionality - that's probably a better place to continue this discussion. ","created_at":"2017-02-05T11:36:04.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/10687#issuecomment-277514146","id":277514146,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/10687","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI3NzUxNDE0Ng==","updated_at":"2017-02-05T11:36:04.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/277514146","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/looeee\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/looeee\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/5307958?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/looeee","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/looeee\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/looeee","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/looeee\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjUzMDc5NTg=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/looeee\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/looeee\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/looeee\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"looeee","type":"User","id":5307958,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/looeee\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/looeee\/orgs"}},{"index":5,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"@looeee I don't claim at App. I think this is awesome idea. But we should understand what can be in three.js and what can't (should be, but not in the library's structure). **three.js** is already over **1Mb** and adding a lot of cool, but unnecessary classes will make it even bigger","created_at":"2017-02-05T11:45:30.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/10687#issuecomment-277514583","id":277514583,"issue_url":"https